Veteran actor, Richard Mofe Damijo aka RMD is full of gratitude and thanks on his 61st birthday. The widely celebrated movie act on Wednesday shared amazing photos via his Instagram page to commemorate his birth. RMD expressed gratitude and thanks to God for the grace bestowed upon him and his family staff, friends, business partners as well as the creative industry that have given him immense joy and opportunities to exhibit his gifts. He also noted birthdays are a chance to look back and forward and reflect on one’s life.   Yemi Alade groans over butt-induced inconvenience     MI Abaga seeks financial support for ailing Eedris Abdul…     Moving abroad changed my life – Wakawaka Doctor   The stylist sexagenarian wrote: “This is 61 and counting! Super grateful and thankful for God’s grace upon my life. “Birthdays are a chance to look back and forward and all I see is God’s grace upon the life of this shy Warri boy that said yes to life. “Grateful for family, staff, friends and business partners and the hands in the creative industry that have given me so much joy and opportunities to shoot my shot!” “To all July babies BIG ENERGY all through this perfect month,” he added.